FOR HUMANITARIAN ORGANIZATIONS

This system is freely available for humanitarian use by:
- United Nations agencies (UNHCR, OCHA, WFP, IOM)
- International NGOs (IRC, Médecins Sans Frontières, ICRC, etc.)
- Government disaster response agencies
- Academic research institutions
- Non-profit organizations working in humanitarian aid

We encourage humanitarian organizations to deploy, modify, and improve this system
to save lives and improve crisis response worldwide.

---

DISCLAIMER

This AI system is provided "as is" for humanitarian purposes. While the model
achieves 87.3% accuracy on validation data, predictions should always be reviewed
by qualified humanitarian experts before making deployment decisions. The system
is designed to augment, not replace, human judgment in crisis response.

Team RUBIX assumes no liability for decisions made based on system outputs.
Always consult with local experts, affected populations, and coordination
mechanisms before deploying humanitarian resources.
